    <intervention_type>Device</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>HM II (HeartMate II LVAD)</intervention_name>
    <description>The HM II pump contains a single moving component, the rotor. The pump is implanted just below the left hemidiaphragm with the inflow attached to the apex of the left ventricle and the outflow graft anastomosed to the ascending aorta. Blood is pumped continuously throughout the cardiac cycle from the left ventricle to the aorta.</description>
    <arm_group_label>HM II (HeartMate II LVAD)</arm_group_label>
    <other_name>Left Ventricular Assist Device</other_name>
  </intervention>
